<!-- The document content area with serialized nodes -->

<TextWithNodes><Node id="0" />Talks aimed at extricating the founders from troubled ambulance chaser <Node id="71" />Claims Direct<Node id="84" /> were continuing <Node id="101" />last night<Node id="111" /> after the company asked for more time to clinch a deal with an unidentified third party.
<Node id="201" />The company, which is the subject of a <Node id="240" />Department of Trade and Industry<Node id="272" /> investigation, is in talks to buy out founders <Node id="320" />Tony Sullman<Node id="332" /> and <Node id="337" />Colin Poole<Node id="348" />, who in turn are trying to buy the <Node id="384" />57%<Node id="387" /> of the company they do not already own through a <Node id="437" />10p<Node id="440" />-a-share offer.<Node id="455" />

<Node id="457" />This week<Node id="466" />, the non-executive directors of <Node id="499" />Claims Direct<Node id="512" /> asked <Node id="519" />Mr Poole<Node id="527" /> and <Node id="532" />Mr Sullman<Node id="542" /> to resign from the company, which was floated on the stock market in <Node id="612" />July last year<Node id="626" /> at <Node id="630" />180p<Node id="634" />. <Node id="636" />Yesterday<Node id="645" /> the shares were trading at <Node id="673" />11p<Node id="676" />.<Node id="677" />

<Node id="679" />The two men, who have created a vehicle, <Node id="720" />Barker Securities<Node id="737" />, to take the company private, have refused to leave.<Node id="790" />

<Node id="792" />The company is understood to be talking to an existing investor, <Node id="857" />Simon Ware-Lane<Node id="872" />, about buying out the two founders, who have been accused by the non-executives of a "cynical attempt" to buy the company too cheaply.<Node id="1007" />

<Node id="1009" />Claims Direct<Node id="1022" /> admitted <Node id="1032" />yesterday<Node id="1041" /> that it had missed its own deadline for arranging an alternative deal to put to investors ahead of the next official stage of the bid already tabled by <Node id="1194" />Barker Securities<Node id="1211" />.<Node id="1212" />

<Node id="1214" />Yesterday<Node id="1223" /> the company asked for more time to continue the talks.<Node id="1278" />

<Node id="1280" />"These discussions with a third party are continuing and the independent directors believe that it is in the best interests of shareholders for them to be progressed," the company said. It was unable to confirm that <Node id="1496" />Barker<Node id="1502" /> had agreed to give them more time.<Node id="1537" />

<Node id="1539" />The company ran into problems with its "no win, no fee" personal injury operation following a court judgment over how much an insurer should be allowed to claim.<Node id="1700" />

<Node id="1702" />Co-operative Insurance Society<Node id="1732" /> <Node id="1733" />yesterday<Node id="1742" /> piled more potential problems on <Node id="1776" />Claims Direct<Node id="1789" /> by saying it would offer free "before the event" insurance to its customers.<Node id="1866" /></TextWithNodes>
